# Homework Portal – Project Rule

## Stack

- **Next.js** (App Router) + React + TypeScript
- **Prisma** + PostgreSQL
- **Auth**: NextAuth or Supabase Auth (email/password or passwordless)
- **File storage**: S3-compatible (e.g. AWS S3, Cloudflare R2) for syllabi; never rely on ephemeral disk
- **Hosting**: Railway (web service + Postgres add-on)

## Multi-tenancy

Every record is scoped by `userId`. In all API routes and server actions:

- Resolve `userId` from the session; return 401 if unauthenticated
- Filter all DB queries by `userId` (e.g. `where: { userId }`)
- Return 404/403 when accessing another user's resources

## Data model (Prisma)

| Model | Key fields |
|-------|------------|
| User | id, email, name |
| GeminiConfig | userId, encryptedApiKey, modelName |
| Course | userId, populiCourseCode?, title, term, meetingScheduleJson |
| Syllabus | userId, courseId, storagePath, originalFilename, uploadStatus |
| Assignment | userId, courseId, title, type, description, dueDate, estimatedTimeMinutes, source |
| WidgetConfig | userId, theme, timeWindow, showCourses |

## Security

- **Gemini API keys**: Encrypt at rest (e.g. `APP_ENCRYPTION_KEY`); decrypt only in server-side code
- **Never** send API keys to the client; only backend routes / server actions use them
- Rate-limit AI endpoints per user and globally

## File structure

- `app/(auth)/` – login, register
- `app/(app)/` – protected layout; dashboard, courses, assignments, settings, widget
- `app/api/` – API routes; all require session and enforce `userId` scoping
- `app/api/widget/today`, `app/api/widget/week` – read-only JSON for lockscreen clients
- `prisma/schema.prisma` – single source of truth for models

## Conventions

- Use server actions or API routes for mutations; keep client components thin
- Widget endpoints return compact JSON: `{ items: [{ title, courseTitle, dueDate, remainingMinutes }] }`
- Syllabus parsing: backend-only; store status on `Syllabus.uploadStatus`; allow re-parse on failure
